minmax(350px, 1fr) forces cards wider than viewport on phones under 400px wide. iPhone SE (375px - 48px padding = 327px available) gets horizontal scrollbar.

Fix: Switch to mobile-first approach:
1. Default .cards grid to grid-template-columns: 1fr (single column)
2. At min-width: 640px, enable auto-fill with minmax(300px, 1fr)
3. At min-width: 1440px, optionally allow 4 columns

Current (base.html ~line 330):
.cards { grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(350px, 1fr)); }

Recommended:
.cards { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 1rem; }
@media (min-width: 640px) {
  .cards { grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(300px, 1fr)); gap: 1.5rem; }
}

