WCAG requirement. No prefers-reduced-motion media query anywhere in the project. All animations (swipe gestures, card rotations, fly-off, hover lifts, spring curves) run at full speed regardless of user preference.

Implementation:
1. Add global CSS rule in base.html that kills animation-duration and transition-duration
2. Add JS awareness in discover.html: check window.matchMedia('(prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)')
3. Skip wind-up animation, card rotation, and use instant transitions when reduced motion preferred
4. Test with macOS accessibility settings

CSS rule for base.html:
@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  *, *::before, *::after {
    animation-duration: 0.01ms !important;
    animation-iteration-count: 1 !important;
    transition-duration: 0.01ms !important;
    scroll-behavior: auto !important;
  }
}

JS additions for discover.html:
- const prefersReducedMotion = window.matchMedia('(prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)').matches;
- Skip wind-up in swipeCard()
- Zero rotation in drag()
- Instant speed in completeSwipe()

